<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Petitions & Advocacy | Navigator +</title>
    <%- include('partials/styles.ejs') %>
    <style>
        body { padding-top: 86px; }
        .petition-card { background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: var(--radius-panel); padding: 26px; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(15,42,30,0.07); margin-bottom: 22px; }
        .petition-card h5 { font-family: var(--font-display); color: var(--ink); }
        .petition-meta { font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink-muted); margin-bottom: 10px; }
        .tag { display: inline-block; background: rgba(29,179,168,0.1); color: var(--brand-teal-deep); font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; padding: 3px 12px; border-radius: 999px; margin-right: 6px; border: 1px solid rgba(29,179,168,0.2); }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar.ejs', { page: 'petitions' }) %>

    <div class="page-hero text-center">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="display-6">Petitions & Advocacy</h1>
            <p class="mx-auto">Road safety in Singapore isn't only shaped by policy — everyday citizens have pushed for change too. Here's some of that history.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container mt-4 mb-5">

        <%- include('partials/readAloud.ejs') %>

        <div id="readable-content">
        <div class="petition-card">
            <span class="tag">Road Safety</span><span class="tag">2026</span>
            <h5>"Implement Stricter Penalties for Errant Drivers and Improve Road Design in Singapore"</h5>
            <div class="petition-meta">Link: <a href="https://www.change.org/p/implement-stricter-penalties-for-errant-drivers-and-improve-road-design-in-singapore" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Petition · Implement Stricter Penalties for Errant Drivers and Improve Road Design in Singapore - Singapore, Singapore · Change.org</a></div>
            <p><strong>Organiser:</strong> A member of the public through Change.org, launched after several high-profile fatal traffic accidents.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong> Increase penalties for dangerous and reckless driving, improve road and junction design, strengthen protection for pedestrians and cyclists, and reduce fatalities.</p>
            <p><strong>Who could participate:</strong> Any member of the public could sign the petition and share it on social media or within community networks.</p>
            <p><strong>Potential outcome:</strong> The petition helped raise public discussion and contributed to later government moves to strengthen traffic enforcement and penalties.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="petition-card">
            <span class="tag">Advocacy</span><span class="tag">2026</span>
            <h5>"Singapore Road Safety Month 2026"</h5>
            <div class="petition-meta">Link: <a href="https://www.mha.gov.sg/media-room/newsroom/launch-of-the-singapore-road-safety-month/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MHA / SRSC</a></div>
            <p><strong>Organisers:</strong> Singapore Road Safety Council, Traffic Police, Ministry of Home Affairs, and partners.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong> Encourage safer road-user behaviour, raise awareness of speeding, distracted driving, and drink-driving, and promote shared responsibility among motorists, cyclists, and pedestrians.</p>
            <p><strong>Who could participate:</strong> Residents could join community road-safety events, educational activities, volunteer programmes, and awareness campaigns.</p>
            <p><strong>Potential outcome:</strong> Increased public awareness and stronger support for ongoing road-safety measures.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="petition-card">
            <span class="tag">Volunteerism</span><span class="tag">Ongoing</span>
            <h5>"Friends of SRSC Volunteer Programme"</h5>
            <div class="petition-meta">Link: <a href="https://www.srsc.org.sg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Singapore Road Safety Council</a></div>
            <p><strong>Organiser:</strong> Singapore Road Safety Council.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong> Build a grassroots road-safety movement, educate communities, and support safety outreach events.</p>
            <p><strong>Who could participate:</strong> Residents could volunteer, join campaigns, and help spread road-safety messages.</p>
            <p><strong>Potential outcome:</strong> Ongoing community engagement and awareness-building.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="petition-card">
            <span class="tag">Public Advocacy</span><span class="tag">2025</span>
            <h5>"Public Advocacy Following 2025 Traffic Fatalities"</h5>
            <div class="petition-meta">Link: <a href="https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/avoidable-deaths-silly-excuses-selfish-behaviour-why-singapores-road-culture-needs-to-change" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The Straits Times</a></div>
            <p><strong>Organisers:</strong> Not a formal petition; it was driven by journalists, road-safety advocates, victims' families, and members of the public.</p>
            <p><strong>Objectives:</strong> Push for cultural change among drivers, increase accountability, and support stricter road-safety measures.</p>
            <p><strong>Who could participate:</strong> People could write letters to newspapers, join online discussions, support petitions, and take part in community advocacy.</p>
            <p><strong>Potential outcome:</strong> Greater public attention on road safety and stronger support for legislative reform.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="petition-card">
            <h5>Why this matters for youth</h5>
            <p>These petitions show that road safety policy in Singapore has never been decided by the government alone — public pressure and citizen advocacy have directly shaped rules like the 2019 PMD footpath ban and pushed for reforms still being debated today, including 2026's proposed changes to drink-driving limits and dangerous driving penalties. If you care about a road safety issue, platforms like Change.org and your Member of Parliament's Meet-the-People sessions are real channels for youth voices to be heard.</p>
        </div>
        </div><!-- /#readable-content -->

    </div>

    <%- include('partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>
</html>
